messages.text: I know you probably can’t forgive me...
but I’m really happy to hear from you.
I don’t blame you for anything, Ada.
You’re no more responsible for what you are...
than I am for what Seth made me.
And what is that, Adam? What are we?
No, I mean you and I are not the same -
I’m not angry. I’m being clinical.
Being locked in the lab gave me a chance to look into my father’s work.
I think he created me too.
No. He altered you. You’re still human.
An evolutionary leap, not a step.
I was made from scratch...you could say.
Everything about this – you and I, this virus – has to do with genome construction...
The combination of genes you and I possess result in a superior genome.
You’re saying we have traits that are beyond human?
I’m saying you and I lack many of the flaws.
I don’t know exactly what differentiates you from me...
Because we’ll continue to evolve as we grow.
But I do know you’re vulnerable to Uncle Noah.
He is the only infected who attacked me.
All the rest fled like mice when I came near.
Noah wasn’t infected. He was vaccinated.
The vaccine your mother injected you with...
it's the same one Seth gave to Noah and to me.
I’ll make it very simple, because I NEED you to understand.
I don’t like where this is going.
The vaccine developed from your DNA makes people like you and me even stronger.
People with altered – and I guess you could say superior – genes.
And he’s immune to the cure that saved your mother.
It took a week for the vaccine to manifest as a disease in Noah.
You’re telling me this isn’t over?
I’m saying it hasn’t even begun.
Every person who has been vaccinated in the last few days...will turn.
That’s over two billion people so far.
I have to contact my mother.
And I need to get you to her.
I was coming to let you out, anyway.
I don’t care what Seth said.
I should never have locked you in there in the first place.
And so is Noah. And so is Seth.
He injected himself with the vaccine he made with your blood...
before that commander looking guy shot him...so yes
Seth is still alive. But he's no longer my father.
This isn’t going to be the same thing you just lived through.
And it’s going to be much worse.
